                                  <div class="article-title-header">
                                        <h1 class="title">The Innovative State</h1>
                                          <h2 class="article-field-subtitle">Governments Should Make Markets, Not Just Fix Them</h2>
                                      </div>
                                                  <div class="article-author-header">
                                                              <div class="article-field-authors">
                        By <a href="/author/mariana-mazzucato">Mariana Mazzucato</a>                      </div>
                                                              <div class="article-field-authors-bio">
                        <p>MARIANA MAZZUCATO is Professor of the Economics of Innovation in the Science Policy Research Unit at the University of Sussex. She is the author of <a href="http://www.amazon.com/Entrepreneurial-State-Debunking-Private-Economics/dp/0857282522/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1418255036&amp;sr=8-1&amp;keywords=Entrepreneurial+State%3A+Debunking+Public+vs.+Private+Sector+Myths"><strong><em>The Entrepreneurial State: Debunking Public vs. Private Sector Myths</em></strong></a>.</p>
<a href="/author/mariana-mazzucato" class="author-link">See more by this author</a>                      </div>
                    
                                          <div class="article-field-issue">
                        From our <a href="/issues/2015/94/1">January/February 2015 Issue</a>                      </div>
                                      </div>
                
                                  <div class="article-field-image">
                    <div class="article-image-wrapper"><img src="http://www.foreignaffairs.com/files/imagecache/800x/images/Mazzucato_InnovativeState.jpg" alt="" title=""  class="" width="800" height="500" /><div class="data-wrapper"><span class="photo-caption"></span><span class="photo-credit"> (Kevin Lamarque / Courtesy Reuters)</span></div></div>                  </div>
                

                                              </div> <!-- /#content-header -->
            
            
            
            <div id="content-area">
              <div id="content-main-area">
